00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:17,497
-so please wait just a little longer.
-I can't imagine what it would be like.

249
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,734
-I want to open it.
-No, you can't.

250
00:13:21,801 --> 00:13:23,169
You shouldn't open it.

251
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:25,104
-I shouldn't?
-No.

252
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:27,407
I understand, though.

253
00:13:27,473 --> 00:13:30,576
Even as a Korean, I want to open it.
So of course he'd want to.

254
00:13:31,444 --> 00:13:35,148
If you try opening it and the owner
catches you, you might get kicked out.

255
00:13:35,214 --> 00:13:36,949
There are places like that in Korea.

256
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:39,986
-Really? They're that strict?
-Yes, some owners

257
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:41,154
are very particular.

258
00:13:41,220 --> 00:13:43,690
-If I open it…
-They'll start scolding you.

259
00:13:43,756 --> 00:13:45,758
It's like a cultural debate!

260
00:13:46,859 --> 00:13:49,729
-At this point…
-Yes.

261
00:13:50,697 --> 00:13:52,365
…the temptation is strong.

262
00:13:53,566 --> 00:13:55,435
-I want to open it.
-You can't.

263
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:57,370
You have to hold it in and let it pass.

264
00:13:57,437 --> 00:13:59,806
Just let me eat freely!

265
00:14:00,707 --> 00:14:02,442
No!

266
00:14:03,409 --> 00:14:05,078
All the waiting we've done until now

267
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:06,713
